  "body": "Opening this up to track state management service related todos\r\n\r\n### Local setup checks\r\n- [x] eth1 mock RPC with 64 validators with finality over 100 epochs\r\n- [x] eth1 mock RPC with 16384 validators with finality over 100 epochs\r\n- [x] Verify one can query historical state with eth1 mock RPC setup. From genesis epoch to latest epoch \r\n- [x] Check profiling for the above\r\n\r\n### Cluster checks\r\n- [x] Verify a node can sync using a fresh DB\r\n- [x] Verify a node can sync to head using an existing DB\r\n- [x] Verify 2000 validators can perform with a node running new state mgmt service\r\n- [x] Check profiling for the above\r\n\r\n\r\n### Misc improvements and pending bugs\r\n- [x] Add a fall back path for unknown state summary incase people switch on/off new state service\r\n- [x] Better handling when epoch boundary root is skipped\r\n- [x] Solve initial sync error: `panic: could not process block: could not get pre state for slot 351241: unknown boundary state`\r\n- [x] Solve initial sync error: `could not save state: could not verify epoch boundary root has state: could not compute epoch boundary state: could not replay blocks: could not process block: could not process block header: parent root does not match the latest block header signing root in state` \r\n\r\n### Production readiness\r\n- [x] Benchmark numbers for worst case state gen for both cold and hot sections\r\n- [ ] Deprecate current archival usages \r\n\r\nDesign doc:\r\nhttps://hackmd.io/-XUMOlKkToS6PRiGC9Vljw",
